The paper focuses on optimizing ordered parallel graph algorithms using a domain-specific language called GraphIt. This involves program analyses, transformations, and code generation to produce fast implementations of ordered parallel graph algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). 

The paper also introduces a new performance optimization called bucket fusion, which fuses together different rounds of ordered algorithms to reduce synchronization overhead. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.PF (Performance). 

Additionally, the paper deals with graph applications and algorithms, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
